data.content:
## What breaks in .NET 11

**Sync I/O on the Cosmos DB provider is fully removed.** In .NET 10 you could opt in to sync-over-async, but in EF Core 11 that opt-in no longer exists. Every synchronous call **always throws** â€” no workaround.

All four methods in your repository are affected:

```csharp
// All of these throw at runtime in EF Core 11:
_context.Products.ToList();
_context.Products.First(p => p.Id == id);
_context.Products.Count();
_context.SaveChanges();
```

**Fix:** Convert to async equivalents and make the methods `async Task`-returning:

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);
    }

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.CountAsync();
    }

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

This will ripple through your call chain â€” all callers must also become `async`/`await`. There is no opt-in flag to restore the old sync behavior.

**Tracking issue:** https://github.com/dotnet/efcore/issues/37059
